│ unswitched successors. However, in the partial-branch unswitch path (the else │
│ case beginning at line ~2459), we perform DT updates and cloning updates, but │
│ do not perform any MemorySSA edge/phi cleanup analogous to the FullUnswitch   │
│ path.                                                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ When partially unswitching a branch, the code rewrites the terminator in the  │
│ split block to direct traffic to the cloned preheader vs the original         │
│ preheader. However, unlike FullUnswitch, it does not:                         │
│ - Remove duplicate incoming edges between ParentBB and RetainedSuccBB nor     │
│ ParentBB and unswitched successors in PHIs via                                │
│ MSSAU->removeDuplicatePhiEdgesBetween.                                        │
│ - Remove now-dead edges from ParentBB to the unswitched successors via        │
│ MSSAU->removeEdge.                                                            │
│ Without these MemorySSA updates, the cloned loop phis (and possibly original  │
│ loop phis) can retain duplicate or stale incoming edges. This leads to        │
│ MemoryDef/Use nodes that no longer have proper dominance relative to their    │
│ uses – exactly the assertion reported by                                      │
│ MemorySSA::verifyOrderingDominationAndDefUses.                                │
│                                                                               │
│ Given the reproducer involves a loop with a single branch (nontrivial         │
│ unswitching condition) and malloc in the body, the MSSA structure is          │
│ sensitive to PHI incoming edges and the cloned loop’s entry. The asymmetry    │
│ between FullUnswitch and partial unswitch in MemorySSA maintenance is the     │
│ most likely cause. The code in the FullUnswitch path shows the required       │
│ MemorySSA cleanup, but the partial path lacks it.                             │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                     │
│ We should add the equivalent MemorySSA cleanup operations to the partial      │
│ unswitching path, immediately after we apply DT updates and perform MSSA      │
│ cloning updates, mirroring the FullUnswitch path. Specifically:               │
│ - Call MSSAU->removeDuplicatePhiEdgesBetween(ParentBB, RetainedSuccBB).       │
│ - For each unswitched successor in UnswitchedSuccBBs, call                    │
│ MSSAU->removeDuplicatePhiEdgesBetween(ParentBB, SuccBB).                      │
│ - For each unswitched successor in UnswitchedSuccBBs, call                    │
│ MSSAU->removeEdge(ParentBB, SuccBB).                                          │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit point:                                                                   │
│ File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/SimpleLoopUnswitch.cpp                       │
│ Around lines 2475-2484 (partial unswitch path MSSAU section), insert the      │
│ following MemorySSA maintenance mirroring the FullUnswitch path:              │
│                                                                               │
│ --- Begin patch description ---                                               │
│ After:                                                                        │
│   DT.applyUpdates(DTUpdates);                                                 │
│   DTUpdates.clear();                                                          │
│                                                                               │
│ and after the existing MSSAU->updateForClonedLoop(...) and                    │
│ MSSAU->updateExitBlocksForClonedLoop(...), add:                               │
│                                                                               │
│   // Remove all but one edge to the retained block and all unswitched         │
│   // blocks to keep cloned PHIs consistent with the new CFG.                  │
│   MSSAU->removeDuplicatePhiEdgesBetween(ParentBB, RetainedSuccBB);            │
│   for (BasicBlock *SuccBB : UnswitchedSuccBBs)                                │
│     MSSAU->removeDuplicatePhiEdgesBetween(ParentBB, SuccBB);                  │
│                                                                               │
│   // Remove all edges to unswitched blocks.                                   │
│   for (BasicBlock *SuccBB : UnswitchedSuccBBs)                                │
│     MSSAU->removeEdge(ParentBB, SuccBB);                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ This mirrors the FullUnswitch path’s MemorySSA cleanup and ensures MemorySSA  │
│ def-use and dominance invariants are preserved after partial unswitching.     │
│ --- End patch description ---                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash stems from incomplete MemorySSA maintenance in the partial          │
│ unswitching branch of SimpleLoopUnswitch. Adding the missing                  │
│ removeDuplicatePhiEdgesBetween and removeEdge calls after cloning updates in  │
│ the partial path makes MemorySSA consistent with the modified CFG, preserving │
│ the dominance of defs over uses and preventing the verification assertion     │
│ from triggering. This fix aligns the partial path with the robust handling    │
│ already present in the FullUnswitch path and should resolve the provided      │
│ reproducer.                                                                   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
